version 2.2.1 (11/16/2012)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	* Fix a bug where X-Sync mode wasn't considered stream data if there
	  wasn't any framing
	* Fix a data loss bug in transparent mode
	* Improved debug prints

version 2.2.0 (10/09/2012)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	* Add install option to Makefile
	* Improve debug prints
	* Fix typos
	* Include the gui, cli and pyfscc into the project
	* Add some 'get' ioctls
	* Add additional examples
	* Rename flush{tx,rx} to purge{tx,rx}
	* Update licenses
	* Added fscc.rules file
	* Fixed a bug causing the number of frames to be incorrect
	* Add driver specific registers to sysfs when in debug mode
	* Fix an issue where a frame was left in the FIFO
	* Optimize the memory consumtion while in streaming mode
	* Fixes setting the clock on older green cards.

version 2.1.3 (02/06/2012)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	* Fix typos
	* Remove sudo from install_tools
	* Remove make all
	* Add default transmit_modifiers
	* Add tx_modifiers and ignore_timeout to sysfs
	* Rearrange initialization code
	* Use sema_init exclusively
	* Clean up code
	* See changesets for full list of changes

version 2.1.2 (09/14/2011)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	* init_MUTEX(x) removed in 2.6.37, I replaced it with sema_init(x,1)

version 2.1.1 (07/19/2011)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	* Fix bug that caused the SuperFSCC/4-LVDS to not install correctly

version 2.1.0 (05/02/2011)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	* Fix comments in code
	* Add make help target
	* Migrate from google code to bitbucket
	* Added code and examples for various transmit modes
	* Fixed dma insmod parameter
	* Add SuperFSCC-LVDS and SuperFSCC/104 to the driver
	* See changesets for full list of changes

version 2.0.5 (02/17/2011)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	* Add a force_fifo option that prevents DMA operation
	* Add a simple example showing how to use the select() function to 
	  determine how much data is available in the card
	  

version 2.0.4 (02/09/2011)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Bugfix release targeting old DMA APIs.

	* Fix a build error with kernels prior to 2.6.27 that used an older dma 
	  mapping function than we currently use
	* Added a makefile command for removing the C headers
	* Added a script to soft link against our sysfs directory
	* Added a script to easily download related software
	* Updated the README to address some confusing sections
	  

version 2.0.3 (01/13/2011)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Bugfix release clarifying what should be considered "streaming" data.

	* Don't consider being in transparent mode as necessarily being streaming
	  data
	

version 2.0.2 (01/12/2011)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Version number update.

	* Synchronize version number of module with repo.
	

version 2.0.1 (01/12/2011)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Bugfix release targeting transparent mode.

	* Add memory constraint checks when in transparent mode
	* Use atomic memory allocation when in transparent mode


version 2.0.0 (01/07/2011)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This is the initial release of the 2.0 driver series.
